00:00:41.170 --> 00:00:43.590
David Levithan.

00:00:43.590 --> 00:00:46.300
David has been a pioneer
in expanding the role

00:00:46.300 --> 00:00:49.160
of gay characters
in teen literature.

00:00:49.160 --> 00:00:52.850
His first novel, <i>Boy Meets Boy</i>
, started as a story he wrote

00:00:52.850 --> 00:00:55.270
for friends for Valentine's Day.

00:00:55.270 --> 00:00:58.420
His other acclaimed
fiction includes <i>Every Day,</i>

00:00:58.420 --> 00:01:01.710
<i>Another Day, </i>and
<i>Two Boys Kissing.</i>

00:01:01.710 --> 00:01:04.480
His best-selling
collaborations include <i>Nick</i>

00:01:04.480 --> 00:01:08.920
<i>and Norah's Infinite Playlist</i>
written with Rachel Cohn,

00:01:08.920 --> 00:01:12.880
and <i>Will Grayson, Will Grayson</i>
written with John Green.

00:01:12.880 --> 00:01:14.670
His latest novel is <i>Sam</i>

00:01:14.670 --> 00:01:18.730
<i>and Ilsa's Last Hurrah </i>also
written with Rachel Cohn.

00:01:18.730 --> 00:01:22.280
In 2016, David was
named the recipient

00:01:22.280 --> 00:01:25.260
of the Margaret A. Edward's
Award for his contribution

00:01:25.260 --> 00:01:27.330
to young adult literature.

00:01:27.330 --> 00:01:31.200
His forthcoming book for
young adults is <i>Someday.</i>

00:01:31.200 --> 00:01:34.770
When not writing during
spare hours on weekends,

00:01:34.770 --> 00:01:38.370
Levithan is Editorial
Director at Scholastic

00:01:38.370 --> 00:01:42.940
and the founding editor of The
Push and Print which is devoted

00:01:42.940 --> 00:01:48.370
to finding new voices and new
authors in teen literature.

00:01:48.370 --> 00:01:50.170
And here he is.

00:01:50.170 --> 00:01:56.230
